==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spark gap
<hw>Spark gap</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The space filled with air or
other dielectric between high potential terminals (as of an
electrostatic machine, induction coil, or condenser), through which the
discharge passes; the air gap of a jump spark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sparkish</ent>⟦br⟧
